The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
Archives
 LOOSE CHANGE
																								 Sahara Mutual Fund has declared a tax-free dividend of 50 per cent under its Sahara Midcap Fund. It is an open-ended equity scheme that invests primarily in mid cap stocks. The selection of stocks is based upon sound financial and business fundamentals. The scheme also has the facility of systematic investment plan to counter volatility and invest regularly. The net asset value of the fund is Rs 20.4858 under the dividend option.																								 ICICI Lombard General Insurance has launched a medical insurance plan that covers expenditure related to outpatient consultations. The maximum coverage on OPD expenses is Rs 10,000. Under this policy, the insurance premium remains the same at Rs 15,000 or Rs 20,000 depending upon the age of the insured. The sum insured changes depending on the age and the number of members covered. 																								 Lotus India Mutual Fund has come out with a three-year close-ended equity fund called Lotus India Infrastructure Fund. This fund would be converted into an open-ended fund after three years from the date of allotment. The scheme will invest in a portfolio of equity and equity-related instruments of infrastructure companies. The new fund offer closes on October 24. 
